{# Shared macros for VFS hint fragments across hook templates. #}

{% macro vfs_analysis(file="<file>", sym="<Symbol>") %}
  Read {{ file }}@/symbols/{{ sym }}@/{{ FILE_CALLERS }}    — who calls it (with code context)
  Read {{ file }}@/symbols/{{ sym }}@/{{ FILE_DEPS }}       — what it calls
  Read {{ file }}@/symbols/{{ sym }}@/{{ FILE_REFERENCES }} — all usage sites
{% endmacro %}

{% macro structural_nav(dir="<dir>", file="<file>") %}
  Read {{ dir }}@/{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}  — aggregated view of all files and symbols
  ls {{ file }}@/symbols/     — list all symbols in a file
{% endmacro %}

{% macro ssot_reminder(rel) %}
SSOT/DRY check on {{ rel }}: does this change duplicate logic, constants, or patterns that exist elsewhere in the codebase? If yes, stop and extract a shared abstraction before continuing.
{% endmacro %}

{% macro batch_edit_hint() %}
Hint: If you have more symbol edits to make in this file (or across files), use **batch edit staging** instead of sequential writes — it's atomic and validated:
  echo 'new body' >file@/symbols/Foo@/edit/replace    # stage
  echo 1 >file@/symbols/Bar@/edit/delete               # stage
  rm @/edit/staged.diff                                 # apply atomically (returns error if validation fails)
{% endmacro %}
